Introduction

cignature was a seven-member girl group under J9Entertainment. They debuted on February 4, 2020, with the digital single "Nun Nu Nan Na".

On January 22, the official debut schedule for their debut lead single "Nun Nu Nan Na" was released. The group's promotional photos were released from January 27 to 28th, with the MV teaser being released on January 30 and the dance practice on the 31st. On February 3, the official music video of their first digital single "Nun Nu Nan Na" was released. Lastly, the single was released on February 4th on various music sites and their debut showcase, "Cignature Move", was held that same day.

On April 27, 2021, J9 Entertainment announced both Sunn and YeAh had left the group and terminated their contracts.

On June 14, 2021, J9 announced the addition of members Chloe and Dohee.

On July 17, 2023, HyeonJu (formerly known as Belle) was announced as a contestant on the SBS survival show Universe Ticket. During the show's finale, she was ranked 6th making her a member and the leader of the project girl group UNIS.

On December 3, 2024, C9 Entertainment announced the group's disbandment along with the termination of all members' contracts.
